The Express,

1013
01:06:44,488 --> 01:06:45,526
show us you care...

1014
01:06:45,595 --> 01:06:46,841
picture of a grumpy Queen.

1015
01:06:47,668 --> 01:06:50,556
The Mail, let the
flag fly at half mast...

1016
01:06:50,618 --> 01:06:53,983
and inside... the Queen should
be here to show her respect.

1017
01:06:55,220 --> 01:06:56,282
But the flip side is,

1018
01:06:56,937 --> 01:07:00,045
they're more popular now...
than Churchill's chocolate.

1019
01:07:00,527 --> 01:07:02,727
Did any of them pick up
on our statement of support?

1020
01:07:02,788 --> 01:07:03,909
Well, just the one...

1021
01:07:08,067 --> 01:07:10,405
Statements of support,
doesn't sell papers.

1022
01:07:18,649 --> 01:07:19,323
Ma'am...

1023
01:07:19,721 --> 01:07:20,660
Ma'am...

1024
01:07:22,507 --> 01:07:23,857
the Prime Minister
for you, Ma'am.

1025
01:07:25,604 --> 01:07:27,708
I'm afraid he's rather insisting.

1026
01:07:30,221 --> 01:07:31,348
I'll take it in the kitchen.

1027
01:07:39,429 --> 01:07:41,095
Good morning,
I'm so sorry to disturb you.

1028
01:07:41,156 --> 01:07:43,760
I'm just expecting a
phone call to come through here.

1029
01:07:43,921 --> 01:07:44,631
Out!

1030
01:07:46,528 --> 01:07:47,470
Oh, there it is...

1031
01:07:52,156 --> 01:07:52,810
Thank you.

1032
01:07:59,116 --> 01:08:00,405
Good morning, Prime Minister.

1033
01:08:00,728 --> 01:08:01,474
Good morning, Ma'am.

1034
01:08:02,996 --> 01:08:04,840
You've seen today's headlines?

1035
01:08:05,949 --> 01:08:06,779
Yes, I have.

1036
01:08:07,289 --> 01:08:08,470
Then I'm sure you'll agree...

1037
01:08:09,065 --> 01:08:10,865
the situation has become...

1038
01:08:11,782 --> 01:08:12,677
Quite critical.

1039
01:08:15,990 --> 01:08:16,639
Ma'am?

1040
01:08:18,279 --> 01:08:21,359
A poll that's to be published in
tomorrow's papers...

1041
01:08:21,463 --> 01:08:24,346
suggests that
70 percent of people believe

1042
01:08:24,407 --> 01:08:27,026
that your actions
have damaged the Monarchy.

1043
01:08:28,488 --> 01:08:29,225
And that,

1044
01:08:30,567 --> 01:08:31,605
one in four,

1045
01:08:32,034 --> 01:08:34,785
are now in favour... of abolishing
the Monarchy all together.

1046
01:08:37,185 --> 01:08:38,621
As your Prime Minister...

1047
01:08:39,989 --> 01:08:43,302
I believe it is my
constitutional responsibility...

1048
01:08:44,125 --> 01:08:46,058
to advise the following...

1049
01:09:00,038 --> 01:09:01,384
Is Queen Elizabeth up yet?

1050
01:09:08,843 --> 01:09:09,617
Mummy?

1051
01:09:11,532 --> 01:09:12,188
One...

1052
01:09:13,257 --> 01:09:16,197
fly the flag at half mast
above Buckingham Palace

1053
01:09:16,258 --> 01:09:18,299
and all other
royal residences...

1054
01:09:20,339 --> 01:09:20,913
two...

1055
01:09:20,982 --> 01:09:24,877
leave Balmoral and fly down to London
at the earliest opportunity...

1056
01:09:26,238 --> 01:09:26,901
three...

1057
01:09:28,010 --> 01:09:31,185
pay respects, in person,
at Diana's coffin...

1058
01:09:33,092 --> 01:09:34,035
and four...

1059
01:09:34,549 --> 01:09:36,923
make a statement via
live television...

1060
01:09:36,983 --> 01:09:38,706
to my people and the world.

1061
01:09:40,464 --> 01:09:43,261
Swift prosecution of
these matters might,

1062
01:09:43,805 --> 01:09:44,699
he felt...

1063
01:09:44,904 --> 01:09:47,552
just might...
avert disaster.

1064
01:09:49,046 --> 01:09:51,693
You will have to talk to the
Lord Chamberlain about all this.

1065
01:09:51,895 --> 01:09:52,754
Well I have...

1066
01:09:53,182 --> 01:09:56,182
And to Robert Fellows, and it
seems they both agree with Mr. Blair.

1067
01:09:57,276 --> 01:09:58,213
Oh, I see...

1068
01:09:58,323 --> 01:10:00,955
Something's happened...
there's been a change... some...

1069
01:10:01,936 --> 01:10:03,399
shift in values.

1070
01:10:06,416 --> 01:10:08,481
When you no longer
understand your people, mummy...

1071
01:10:08,542 --> 01:10:11,163
maybe it is time to
hand it over to the next generation?

1072
01:10:11,224 --> 01:10:12,808
Oh, don't be ridiculous...

1073
01:10:13,986 --> 01:10:15,970
Remember the vow you took?

1074
01:10:18,512 --> 01:10:22,116
I declare that my whole life,
whether it be long or short...

1075
01:10:22,218 --> 01:10:24,384
shall be devoted to your service.

1076
01:10:25,996 --> 01:10:27,038
Your whole life.

1077
01:10:27,965 --> 01:10:29,861
That is a commitment to God...

1078
01:10:30,056 --> 01:10:31,242
as well as your people.

1079
01:10:31,303 --> 01:10:33,771
But what if my actions
are damaging the Crown?

1080
01:10:33,832 --> 01:10:35,041
Damaging it!?

1081
01:10:35,998 --> 01:10:39,124
You're the greatest asset
this institution has...

1082
01:10:39,459 --> 01:10:41,473
one of the greatest
it has ever had.

1083
01:10:43,878 --> 01:10:46,857
The problem will come
when you leave...

1084
01:10:47,552 --> 01:10:49,896
but you mustn't think
about that now...

1085
01:10:49,964 --> 01:10:51,245
Certainly not today.

1086
01:10:51,306 --> 01:10:52,431
Oh, mummy...

1087
01:10:53,359 --> 01:10:55,008
You must show your strength...

1088
01:10:55,719 --> 01:10:57,386
reassert your authority.

1089
01:10:59,990 --> 01:11:02,108
You sit on the most
powerful throne in Europe.

1090
01:11:02,903 --> 01:11:07,148
Head of an unbroken line that
goes back more than a thousand years.

1091
01:11:07,641 --> 01:11:11,817
Do you think any of your predecessors
would have dropped everything...

1092
01:11:12,191 --> 01:11:15,537
and gone up to London
because a bunch of hysterics...

1093
01:11:15,598 --> 01:11:18,973
carrying candles,
needed help with their grief?

1094
01:11:21,775 --> 01:11:22,542
As for that...

1095
01:11:23,699 --> 01:11:25,081
silly Mr. Blair...

1096
01:11:26,002 --> 01:11:27,276
with his Cheshire Cat grin...

1097
01:11:42,491 --> 01:11:44,366
Mr. Janvrin on the
phone for you, Sir...

1098
01:11:46,528 --> 01:11:47,369
Yes?

1099
01:11:48,639 --> 01:11:49,388
What?

1100
01:11:50,482 --> 01:11:51,722
I can't hear!

1101
01:11:54,337 --> 01:11:55,228
That's madness...

1102
01:11:56,149 --> 01:11:57,274
the whole thing!

1103
01:11:58,302 --> 01:11:59,618
Bloody madness!

1104
01:12:04,245 --> 01:12:05,537
I've just been told...

1105
01:12:06,822 --> 01:12:07,888
You've...

1106
01:12:08,240 --> 01:12:11,300
decided to follow the Prime
Minister's advise...

1107
01:12:12,482 --> 01:12:13,950
I just want to say, I...

1108
01:12:15,791 --> 01:12:16,916
admire...

1109
01:12:19,980 --> 01:12:21,312
I think it's the right decision.

1110
01:12:23,324 --> 01:12:25,113
Let's hope we haven't
left it too late.

1111
01:13:12,839 --> 01:13:14,923
Clearly The Queen
has had a change of heart...

1112
01:13:14,984 --> 01:13:17,590
she's clearly responding to
the need to feel...

1113
01:13:17,651 --> 01:13:20,628
that the royal family
is somehow engaged.

1114
01:13:21,435 --> 01:13:24,409
These are flowers that have been
brought to the gates of Balmoral...

1115
01:13:24,470 --> 01:13:25,804
so that she can actually see

1116
01:13:25,947 --> 01:13:29,030
some token, of what's been
expressed down here in London...

1117
01:13:29,373 --> 01:13:31,987
-Fish Fingers... do you want any?
-I'll be right there...

1118
01:13:37,750 --> 01:13:39,455
Thank God, for that!

1119
01:14:08,261 --> 01:14:12,157
Britain's Queen Elisabeth will
deliver a televised address Friday...

1120
01:14:12,217 --> 01:14:15,500
the royal family has been accused
of not showing enough remorse...

1121
01:14:15,561 --> 01:14:17,102
over Princess Diana's death...

1122
01:14:38,724 --> 01:14:40,453
Where are the boys?
Have they already left?

1123
01:14:40,664 --> 01:14:41,325
Yes...

1124
01:14:42,226 --> 01:14:44,727
they left for London,
after breakfast, with Charles.

1125
01:14:46,314 --> 01:14:47,726
It's not right, you know...

1126
01:14:47,957 --> 01:14:50,777
No, but further discussion
is no longer helpful, either.

1127
01:14:52,061 --> 01:14:52,909
Oh, well...

1128
01:14:54,619 --> 01:14:58,453
I suppose it does give the ghillies time
to find another stag for the boys.

1129
01:14:59,134 --> 01:15:00,939
-Now there's has been shot.
-What?

1130
01:15:01,608 --> 01:15:02,650
Haven't you heard?

1131
01:15:03,065 --> 01:15:05,169
He wandered over to one
of the neighbouring estates...

1132
01:15:05,848 --> 01:15:07,956
where one of the
commercial guests got him.

1133
01:15:12,491 --> 01:15:13,532
Oh... really?

1134
01:15:15,621 --> 01:15:16,517
Which estate?

1135
01:15:35,240 --> 01:15:36,282
Here's your box.

1136
01:15:37,539 --> 01:15:39,576
There's some policy and
stuff in here that's important.

1137
01:15:39,850 --> 01:15:41,046
Have you seen the papers?

1138
01:15:41,391 --> 01:15:42,710
No, I thought I'd give
them a miss today...

1139
01:15:42,771 --> 01:15:44,003
of course I've seen the papers!

1140
01:15:44,064 --> 01:15:47,155
Not bad, eh... Your Majesty
have come down to London...

1141
01:15:47,350 --> 01:15:49,352
Who says that?
Tony Blair.

1142
01:15:51,878 --> 01:15:53,586
Mr. Father of the nation.

1143
01:16:10,797 --> 01:16:11,463
Ma'am...

1144
01:16:12,705 --> 01:16:14,246
-Good morning, Ma'am.
-Good morning.

1145
01:16:14,723 --> 01:16:16,921
Is it his Lordship,
you've come to see?

1146
01:16:16,982 --> 01:16:20,630
No, please don't disturb him...
I've come on another matter...

1147
01:16:20,691 --> 01:16:21,666
I hope you don't mind?

1148
01:16:44,157 --> 01:16:45,039
There he is...

1149
01:16:47,688 --> 01:16:49,293
A beauty, isn't he?

1150
01:16:50,678 --> 01:16:51,837
An imperial, Ma'am.

1151
01:16:54,638 --> 01:16:56,076
14 pointer.

1152
01:17:05,753 --> 01:17:07,478
-He was wounded?
-Yes...

1153
01:17:08,637 --> 01:17:12,027
We got our guest in very close...
had him lined up perfect.

1154
01:17:13,957 --> 01:17:14,846
And still...

1155
01:17:16,250 --> 01:17:18,650
an investment banker, Ma'am...
from London.

1156
01:17:19,699 --> 01:17:23,227
I'm afraid the stalkers had to
follow him for miles, to finish him off...

1157
01:17:27,087 --> 01:17:28,849
Let's hope he didn't suffer too much.

1158
01:17:39,319 --> 01:17:41,714
Please pass my congratulations,
to your guest.

1159
01:17:41,957 --> 01:17:42,850
I will, Ma'am...

1160
01:17:50,532 --> 01:17:51,498
God bless you, Ma'am.

1161
01:17:52,385 --> 01:17:53,312
Thank you.

1162
01:18:26,664 --> 01:18:27,371
Ma'am?

1163
01:18:28,222 --> 01:18:28,973
Yes, Robin...

1164
01:18:29,517 --> 01:18:32,271
I've done a draft,
of your television address.

1165
01:18:32,905 --> 01:18:33,717
Thank you.

1166
01:18:38,879 --> 01:18:40,046
Was there anything else?

1167
01:18:41,722 --> 01:18:42,572
No, Ma'am.

1168
01:18:43,605 --> 01:18:45,786
Landing in 15 minutes.

1169
01:18:57,223 --> 01:18:58,597
I've got The Queen's speech.

1170
01:19:00,602 --> 01:19:02,959
-Shall I give Tony a copy?
-No, let me have a look at it first...

1171
01:19:03,509 --> 01:19:04,550
He's next door.

1172
01:19:54,600 --> 01:19:59,749
The Queen is getting out of the car...
and is going to talk to people.

1173
01:19:59,849 --> 01:20:03,580
It's extremely unusual...
this is almost unprecedented...

1174
01:20:03,641 --> 01:20:08,070
I think perhaps the last time
The Queen was among her people...

1175
01:20:08,255 --> 01:20:12,252
outside the Palace...
was the day the war in Europe ended.

1176
01:20:35,130 --> 01:20:36,980
They sent a copy
of The Queen's speech...

1177
01:20:39,694 --> 01:20:41,514
Well, let's get the frost off it first.

1178
01:20:49,903 --> 01:20:51,796
I've phoned them
with a couple of suggestions...

1179
01:20:52,429 --> 01:20:54,357
to make it sound like it
came from a human being.

1180
01:20:54,418 --> 01:20:55,223
Yeah, alright Alastair...

1181
01:20:58,338 --> 01:21:01,119
Well at least the old bat has
finally agreed to visit Diana's coffin.

1182
01:21:01,180 --> 01:21:03,993
When you get it wrong,
you really get it wrong...

1183
01:21:04,411 --> 01:21:08,515
that woman has given her
whole life in service to her people.

1184
01:21:09,265 --> 01:21:11,202
50 years doing the job,
she never wanted...

1185
01:21:11,795 --> 01:21:13,816
a job she watched kill her father...

1186
01:21:13,879 --> 01:21:17,934
she's executed it with honour, dignity,
and as far as I could tell...

1187
01:21:17,995 --> 01:21:20,956
without a single blemish,
and now we're all baying for her blood.

1188
01:21:21,263 --> 01:21:23,972
All because she's struggling
to lead the world in mourning

1189
01:21:24,041 --> 01:21:26,853
for someone who threw everything
she offered back in her face.

1190
01:21:26,939 --> 01:21:29,537
And who for the last few years
seemed committed 24/7

1191
01:21:29,696 --> 01:21:32,530
to destroying everything
she holds most dear.

1192
01:22:37,592 --> 01:22:40,779
Hello... would you like
me to place those for you?

1193
01:22:41,132 --> 01:22:41,949
No...

1194
01:22:42,980 --> 01:22:43,853
Oh...

1195
01:22:44,568 --> 01:22:45,991
These are for you.

1196
01:22:48,933 --> 01:22:49,534
For me?

1197
01:22:54,167 --> 01:22:55,076
Thank you.

1198
01:22:56,776 --> 01:22:57,916
Thank you very much.

1199
01:23:28,742 --> 01:23:31,347
There's been a last minute
addition from Downing Street.

1200
01:23:31,408 --> 01:23:34,627
They're suggesting adding,
'and as a grandmother'...

1201
01:23:34,931 --> 01:23:36,285
here.
Right.

1202
01:23:41,957 --> 01:23:46,086
So what I say to you now, as
your Queen, and as a grandmother...

1203
01:23:46,915 --> 01:23:48,388
I say from my heart.

1204
01:23:49,108 --> 01:23:50,191
You think you can say it?

1205
01:23:51,784 --> 01:23:53,968
-Do I have a choice?
-We're ready for you, Your Majesty.

1206
01:23:57,602 --> 01:23:59,571
Just to confirm,
this is going out live.

1207
01:24:00,400 --> 01:24:02,222
-Fine.
-And you'll be at the front of

1208
01:24:02,283 --> 01:24:04,095
the 6 o'clock news...
on all the channels.

1209
01:24:04,244 --> 01:24:04,932
Yes.

1210
01:24:48,556 --> 01:24:51,272
-Okay, nice and quiet...
-Ten seconds, everyone!

1211
01:24:55,332 --> 01:24:58,553
We cross now, live,
to Buckingham Palace...

1212
01:24:58,614 --> 01:25:01,403
for the Queen's tribute
to Princess Diana.

1213
01:25:07,704 --> 01:25:10,251
Since last Sundays'
dreadful news...

1214
01:25:10,327 --> 01:25:13,390
we have seen throughout Britain,
and around the world...

1215
01:25:13,609 --> 01:25:17,252
an overwhelming expression
of sadness at Diana's death.

1216
01:25:19,046 --> 01:25:21,984
We have all been trying,
in our different ways, to cope...

1217
01:25:23,324 --> 01:25:25,886
it is not easy
to express a sense of loss...

1218
01:25:26,214 --> 01:25:28,744
since the initial shock,
is often succeeded

1219
01:25:28,805 --> 01:25:30,579
by a mixture
of other feelings...

1220
01:25:30,752 --> 01:25:33,596
disbelief,
incomprehension, anger...

1221
01:25:33,865 --> 01:25:36,270
and concern for
those who remain.

1222
01:25:38,406 --> 01:25:41,857
We have all felt those
emotions in these last few days...

1223
01:25:42,284 --> 01:25:46,742
so what I say to you now,
as your Queen, and as a grandmother...

1224
01:25:47,824 --> 01:25:49,471
I say from my heart.

1225
01:25:50,585 --> 01:25:52,697
Heart...
What heart?

1226
01:25:53,434 --> 01:25:54,800
She doesn't mean a word of this.

1227
01:25:55,236 --> 01:25:58,029
That's not the point.
What she's doing is extraordinary.

1228
01:26:01,118 --> 01:26:02,187
That's how to survive.

1229
01:26:02,324 --> 01:26:03,389
Listen to you...

1230
01:26:03,868 --> 01:26:07,051
A week ago you were the
great moderniser...

1231
01:26:07,160 --> 01:26:09,784
making speeches
about the people's Princess.

1232
01:26:10,424 --> 01:26:12,424
Now you've gone weak at the knees.

1233
01:26:16,355 --> 01:26:18,547
You know... I don't know
why I'm so surprised...

1234
01:26:19,589 --> 01:26:21,568
At the end of the day,
all Labour Prime Ministers...

1235
01:26:21,629 --> 01:26:23,511
go Ga-Ga for the Queen.

1236
01:26:24,803 --> 01:26:25,307
What?

1237
01:26:32,598 --> 01:26:36,421
I, for one, believe that there are
lessons to be drawn from her life...

1238
01:26:36,854 --> 01:26:40,184
and from the extraordinary,
and moving, reaction to her death.

1239
01:26:42,313 --> 01:26:45,433
I share in your determination,
to cherish her memory.

1240
01:26:46,708 --> 01:26:50,371
I hope that tomorrow we
can all, wherever we are...

1241
01:26:50,583 --> 01:26:53,742
join in expressing our grief,
at Diana's loss...

1242
01:26:54,152 --> 01:26:57,003
and gratitude for her
all too short life.

1243
01:26:58,285 --> 01:27:00,656
May those who died,
rest in peace...

1244
01:27:01,207 --> 01:27:03,599
and may we,
each and everyone of us...

1245
01:27:04,173 --> 01:27:09,361
thank God, for someone who
made many, many people, happy.

1246
01:27:16,632 --> 01:27:19,350
Diana's coffin, now on the move...

1247
01:27:19,548 --> 01:27:21,836
the short distance
from St. James' Palace...

1248
01:27:22,407 --> 01:27:25,279
to her home at Kensington
Palace, for the final night...

1249
01:27:25,439 --> 01:27:27,200
before her burial tomorrow.

1250
01:27:28,642 --> 01:27:29,368
It's incredible...

1251
01:27:30,058 --> 01:27:30,977
less than a week.

1252
01:27:31,857 --> 01:27:33,899
Who could have imagined,
such scenes?

1253
01:28:48,982 --> 01:28:53,050
Diana was the very essence
of compassion, of duty...

1254
01:28:53,727 --> 01:28:55,871
of style, of beauty.

1255
01:28:56,431 --> 01:28:57,999
A very British girl...

1256
01:28:58,060 --> 01:29:00,311
who transcended nationality.

1257
01:29:01,134 --> 01:29:03,279
Someone with
a natural nobility...

1258
01:29:03,435 --> 01:29:07,040
who was classless, and who
proved in the last year...

1259
01:29:07,281 --> 01:29:10,422
that she needed no royal title
to continue to generate...

1260
01:29:10,554 --> 01:29:12,214
a particular brand of magic.

1261
01:29:17,071 --> 01:29:19,398
I would like to end by,
thanking God...

1262
01:29:19,606 --> 01:29:22,440
for the small mercies he's
shown us at this dreadful time...

1263
01:29:23,185 --> 01:29:25,859
for taking Diana at
her most beautiful and radiant.

1264
01:29:26,198 --> 01:29:28,348
And when she had joy,
in her private life.

1265
01:29:29,625 --> 01:29:32,196
Above all, we give thanks
for the life of a woman...

1266
01:29:32,358 --> 01:29:34,756
I'm so proud
to be able to call my sister.

1267
01:29:35,454 --> 01:29:37,391
The unique, the complexed...

1268
01:29:38,146 --> 01:29:40,733
the extraordinary,
and irreplaceable, Diana.

1269
01:29:41,096 --> 01:29:44,235
Who's beauty, both internal
and external...

1270
01:29:44,621 --> 01:29:47,237
will never be extinguished
from our minds.

1271
01:30:42,316 --> 01:30:45,954
-So, off to see your girlfriend?
-Now, now.

1272
01:30:48,916 --> 01:30:51,310
You know, I hope she
shows you some respect this time.

1273
01:30:52,087 --> 01:30:54,294
It's quite a debt of gratitude,
she owes you.

1274
01:30:55,731 --> 01:30:57,781
Mr. Saviour of the Monarchy.

1275
01:30:58,442 --> 01:31:00,088
I doubt she'll see it that way...

1276
01:31:05,907 --> 01:31:07,736
-Robin... good to see you.
-Prime Minister.

1277
01:31:07,797 --> 01:31:08,839
Tony, please.

1278
01:31:20,067 --> 01:31:21,400
The Prime Minister,
Your Majesty.

1279
01:31:30,430 --> 01:31:31,472
Do sit down.

1280
01:31:31,930 --> 01:31:32,771
Thank you.

1281
01:31:46,081 --> 01:31:46,979
It's good to see you again.

1282
01:31:48,654 --> 01:31:51,282
After what's been...
quite a summer.

1283
01:31:52,218 --> 01:31:54,719
I'm referring to your visit
to India... and Pakistan.

1284
01:31:56,204 --> 01:31:58,824
Where your comments on
ending historic disagreements...

1285
01:31:58,885 --> 01:31:59,994
went down very well.

1286
01:32:02,325 --> 01:32:04,366
On the commonwealth heads
of government meeting...

1287
01:32:05,700 --> 01:32:07,097
I spoke to the Prime Minister of Malawi...

1288
01:32:07,540 --> 01:32:09,978
and he was saying
how much he appreciated your...

1289
01:32:10,384 --> 01:32:12,110
tough stands on Nigeria...

1290
01:32:12,594 --> 01:32:14,185
I meant to tell you at the time, but...

1291
01:32:16,014 --> 01:32:17,672
you were being monopolised, rather...

1292
01:32:20,902 --> 01:32:23,194
I imagine those occasions
must be quite difficult.

1293
01:32:24,774 --> 01:32:28,534
24 heads of government, each
clamouring for a private audience.

1294
01:32:33,332 --> 01:32:37,628
Also we have another
chance to speak, since... that week.

1295
01:32:41,203 --> 01:32:42,885
And I wanted to offer my apologies.

1296
01:32:43,465 --> 01:32:44,398
Whatever for?

1297
01:32:44,923 --> 01:32:48,981
In case you felt manhandled, or...
managed, in any way.

1298
01:32:49,042 --> 01:32:50,542
No, not at all.

1299
01:32:56,746 --> 01:32:59,751
I don't think I shall ever understand,
what happened this summer.

1300
01:33:00,164 --> 01:33:04,182
Well... the circumstances
were exceptional, Ma'am...

1301
01:33:05,617 --> 01:33:08,483
And in the end you showed
great personal strength...

1302
01:33:09,016 --> 01:33:10,891
courage and humility.

1303
01:33:11,228 --> 01:33:13,562
You're confusing humility,
with humiliation.

1304
01:33:13,907 --> 01:33:15,115
That's not true.

1305
01:33:15,431 --> 01:33:19,194
You didn't read the cards on the
flowers outside the Palace, that Friday.

1306
01:33:20,103 --> 01:33:23,036
I actually think history will show,
it was a good week for you.

1307
01:33:23,273 --> 01:33:25,315
And an even better one
for you, Mr. Blair.

1308
01:33:26,634 --> 01:33:28,547
But there are 52 weeks
in the year, Ma'am...

1309
01:33:29,745 --> 01:33:33,375
and 2500 in the time
since you've been Queen.

1310
01:33:36,682 --> 01:33:39,205
And when people come
to assess your legacy...

1311
01:33:39,793 --> 01:33:41,827
they won't remember those few days.
Oh, really?

1312
01:33:43,559 --> 01:33:46,808
You don't think what affection
people once had for...

1313
01:33:48,282 --> 01:33:49,567
for this institution...

1314
01:33:50,893 --> 01:33:51,914
has been diminished?

1315
01:33:52,126 --> 01:33:52,805
No...

1316
01:33:53,331 --> 01:33:54,187
not at all.

1317
01:33:55,464 --> 01:33:57,418
You're more respected now,
than ever...

1318
01:33:57,764 --> 01:34:01,391
I gather some of your closest advisers
were less fulsome in their support.

1319
01:34:03,383 --> 01:34:04,617
One or two...

1320
01:34:05,440 --> 01:34:09,284
but as a leader, I could never
have added my voice to that chorus.

1321
01:34:09,345 --> 01:34:10,983
Because you saw those headlines,
and you thought...

1322
01:34:11,044 --> 01:34:12,578
one day that might happen to me.

1323
01:34:15,720 --> 01:34:16,967
And it will, Mr. Blair.

1324
01:34:17,778 --> 01:34:19,650
Quite suddenly, and without warning.

1325
01:34:22,862 --> 01:34:25,172
So... shall we get on
with the business in hand?

1326
01:34:27,338 --> 01:34:28,394
Oh, look...

1327
01:34:30,353 --> 01:34:32,531
I do love this time of day.

1328
01:34:33,024 --> 01:34:34,789
Shall we walk, while there is still light?

1329
01:34:35,048 --> 01:34:38,048
You know the clocks go back
next week, it will be dark before five.

1330
01:34:38,721 --> 01:34:41,133
-I do hope you're a walker?
-I am...

1331
01:34:41,319 --> 01:34:44,748
Good... I always think these meetings
have a far greater chance of success...

1332
01:34:45,017 --> 01:34:46,538
if the Prime Minister is a walker.

1333
01:34:47,590 --> 01:34:49,869
As a matter of fact, that's
how I think best... on my feet...

1334
01:34:50,009 --> 01:34:52,602
I've never been one
for sitting around endlessly...

1335
01:34:52,754 --> 01:34:55,299
a good walk and fresh air
sorts everything out.

1336
01:35:00,918 --> 01:35:04,272
One in four... you said...
wanted to get rid of me.

1337
01:35:04,982 --> 01:35:05,954
For about half an hour.

1338
01:35:06,992 --> 01:35:07,788
But then...

1339
01:35:08,477 --> 01:35:11,095
you came down to London,
and all that went away.

1340
01:35:13,653 --> 01:35:15,639
I've never been hated
like that before.

1341
01:35:16,724 --> 01:35:18,081
Then, that
must have been difficult...

1342
01:35:19,180 --> 01:35:19,900
Yes...

1343
01:35:21,789 --> 01:35:22,563
very.

1344
01:35:26,898 --> 01:35:30,510
Nowadays people want glamour,
and tears, the grand performance.

1345
01:35:31,027 --> 01:35:33,323
I'm not very good at that,
I never have been...

1346
01:35:34,698 --> 01:35:37,197
I prefer to keep
my feelings to myself.

1347
01:35:38,850 --> 01:35:42,345
And foolishly I believed that was
what people wanted from their Queen...

1348
01:35:42,406 --> 01:35:45,292
not to make a fuss, nor wear one's
heart on one's sleeve...

1349
01:35:45,546 --> 01:35:47,880
duty first, self second.

1350
01:35:49,852 --> 01:35:51,399
That's how I was brought up...

1351
01:35:53,349 --> 01:35:54,786
that's all I've ever known.

1352
01:35:55,115 --> 01:35:57,389
You were so young
when you became Queen.

1353
01:36:04,569 --> 01:36:05,306
Yes...

1354
01:36:07,625 --> 01:36:08,725
Yes, a girl.

1355
01:36:15,333 --> 01:36:17,706
But I can see
that the world has changed...

1356
01:36:18,722 --> 01:36:19,535
and one must...

1357
01:36:20,802 --> 01:36:21,830
modernise.

1358
01:36:24,008 --> 01:36:26,524
Well, perhaps that's where I can help.

1359
01:36:28,689 --> 01:36:31,009
Don't get ahead of yourself,
Prime Minister, and remember...

1360
01:36:31,070 --> 01:36:33,219
I am the one
supposed to be advising you.

1361
01:36:38,078 --> 01:36:38,856
Come, dogs!

1362
01:36:47,677 --> 01:36:51,079
Tell me, Mr. Blair, what might we expect
from our first parliament?

1363
01:36:51,599 --> 01:36:56,147
Er... well, ma'am,
top of the list is education.

1364
01:36:56,699 --> 01:36:59,591
We want to reduce classroom sizes.

1365
01:37:00,246 --> 01:37:00,981
Yes.

1366
01:37:02,310 --> 01:37:05,426
And create a lower teacher-pupil ratio.
